{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3573455,"name":"Taj Entabi","username":"tajent","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ac8455/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-30T04:15:39.038Z","cooked":"

Today we did a test run of our new swerve robot, and at first the connection on the radio was very shoddy even though we connected it to a piece of aluminum on the exterior, powered through POE and backed up with direct power from the PDH. After deploying some test code, we found that the robot code indicator stayed red. We reflashed the rio and updated the AP and robot radio to 25.0.0, and nothing worked. Communication flashed between red and green at completely random intervals, and even a blank WPIlib template wouldnt make the robot code turn green.

Heres the test code we ran:
https://github.com/FRC9706/Robot-2025/tree/CompExperimental

Anyone have any ideas about what might be causing this?

What firmware are you putting on the radio?

25.0.0 is not a firmware name/number that is associated with the VH-109/would be a release FAR in the future.

The release version as of 3/29/25 is 1.3.0…

Additionally you should narrow down your variables.

Can you deploy tethered? Can you bring up the radio or Rio web pages? Does each device see the other and have the right IP address (visible through the Rio webpage or arp-a in command line when connected to the robot or for the radio via the network configuration tool for the VH radios)

There’s 3 DIP switches underneath; turn off the one for 2.4GHz wifi.
